13 (xvii) THESEUS 1

King of holy Athens, lord of the soft-living Ionians, what new thing means 'the war-song that eries from the brazen-belled clarion? Doth a captain of enemies beseb2 the bounds of our land? or thieves of ill intent drive our herds of sheep perforce in their keepers' despite? or what is it pricks thy heart? Prithee speak3 for thou, me- thinks, if any man, hast aid of valiant youths to thy hand, O son of Pandion and Creusa.—
